title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\Tensorboard
name: Tensorboard
description:
Tensorboard is a physical database that stores users' training metrics.

A default Tensorboard is provided in each region of a GCP project. If needed users can also create extra Tensorboards in their projects.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Tensorboard

params.name: data.labels
params.description: The labels with user-defined metadata to organize your Tensorboards. Label keys and values can be no longer than 64 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. No more than 64 user labels can be associated with one Tensorboard (System labels are excluded). See https://goo.gl/xmQnxf for more information and examples of labels. System reserved label keys are prefixed with "aiplatform.googleapis.com/" and are immutable.
